{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6217","heading":"Global internet freedom","label":"6217 Global internet freedom","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/ch71","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Department of State Authorization Act of 2022, and also as part of the James M. Inhofe National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2023, and not as part of the United States International Broadcasting Act of 1994 which comprises this chapter.","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsFor definitions of terms used in this section, see , set out as a note under .section 9002 of Pub. L. 117–263section 2651 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Statement of policy","label":"a Statement of policy","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"whose governments restrict freedom of expression on the internet; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that are important to the national interest of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Purpose and coordination with other programs","label":"b Purpose and coordination with other programs","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to counter the development of repressive internet-related laws and regulations, including countering threats to internet freedom at international organizations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to combat violence against bloggers and other civil society activists who utilize the internet; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to enhance digital security training and capacity building for democracy activists;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to research key threats to internet freedom;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to continue the development of technologies that provide or enhance access to the internet, including circumvention tools that bypass internet blocking, filtering, and other censorship techniques used by authoritarian governments; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to maintain the technological advantage of the Federal Government over the censorship techniques described in subparagraph (B); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall be incorporated into country assistance and democracy promotion strategies, as appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"c Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$75,000,000 to the Department and USAID, to continue efforts to promote internet freedom globally, and shall be matched, to the maximum extent practicable, by sources other than the Federal Government, including the private sector; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"for open-source tools and techniques to securely develop and distribute digital content produced by the USAGM and its grantees;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to facilitate audience access to such digital content on websites that are censored;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to coordinate the distribution of such digital content to targeted regional audiences; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fc%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to promote and distribute such tools and techniques, including digital security techniques.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"United States Agency for Global Media activities","label":"d United States Agency for Global Media activities","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Annual certification","label":"1 Annual certification","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have evaluated the risks and benefits of such new tools or techniques; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"have established safeguards to minimize the use of such new tools or techniques for illicit purposes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Information sharing","label":"2 Information sharing","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"sharing information, technologies, and best practices; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"assessing the effectiveness of such technologies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"United States Agency for Global Media","label":"3 United States Agency for Global Media","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"coordinate international broadcasting programs and incorporate such programs into country broadcasting strategies, as appropriate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"solicit project proposals through an open, transparent, and competitive application process, including by seeking input from technical and subject matter experts; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/d/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fd%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"support internet circumvention tools and techniques for audiences in countries that are strategic priorities for the OTF, in accordance with USAGM’s annual language service prioritization review.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"USAGM report","label":"e USAGM report","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the efforts of the Office of Internet Freedom; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the efforts of the Open Technology Fund;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the capacity of internet censorship circumvention tools supported by the Office of Internet Freedom and grantees of the Open Technology Fund that are available for use by individuals in foreign countries seeking to counteract censors; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any barriers to the provision of the efforts described in clauses (i) and (ii) of subparagraph (A), including access to surge funding; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"responding rapidly to internet shutdowns in closed societies; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/e/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fe%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensuring uninterrupted circumvention services for USAGM entities to promote internet freedom within repressive regimes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Joint report","label":"f Joint report","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Department circumvention efforts; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"USAID efforts to support internet infrastructure;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the capacity of internet censorship circumvention tools supported by the Federal Government that are available for use by individuals in foreign countries seeking to counteract censors; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any barriers to provision of the efforts enumerated in clauses (i) and (ii) of subsection (e)(1)(A), including access to surge funding; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to respond rapidly to internet shutdowns in closed societies; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Ff%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to provide internet connectivity to foreign locations where the provision of additional internet access service would promote freedom from repressive regimes.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Security audits","label":"g Security audits","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Before providing any support for open source technologies under this section, such technologies must undergo comprehensive security audits to ensure that such technologies are secure and have not been compromised in a manner that is detrimental to the interest of the United States or to the interests of individuals and organizations benefitting from programs supported by such funding.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":"Surge","label":"h Surge","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"1 Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"are carried out in crisis situations by vetted entities that are already engaged in internet freedom programs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"involve circumvention tools; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"increase the overseas bandwidth for companies that received Federal funding during the previous fiscal year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Certification","label":"2 Certification","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Amounts authorized to be appropriated pursuant to paragraph (1) may not be expended until the Secretary has certified to the appropriate congressional committees, the Committee on Appropriations of the Senate, and the Committee on Appropriations of the House of Representatives that the use of such funds is in the national interest of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":"Defined term","label":"i Defined term","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6217","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft22%2Fs6217%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section, the term “internet censorship circumvention tool” means a software application or other tool that an individual can use to evade foreign government restrictions on internet access.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
